Chocolate Crackle recipe

Ingredients:
4 oz. unsweetened chocolate, melted
1/2 cup vegetable oil
1 1/2 cups sugar 
4 eggs
2 tsp. vanilla extract
1 cup flour 
1 tsp. baking powder
1/2 tsp. salt
1/2 cup powdered sugar

Beat together chocolate, oil, sugar, and eggs. Mix in vanilla extract. Mix flour, baking powder and salt. Slowly beat flour mixture into sugar mixture. Chill for 1-2 hours until dough is pliable and easy to handle. Roll the dough into tablespoon-size balls. Roll the dough-balls in the powdered sugar to coat them. Bake at 350 F for 12-14 minutes on a greased baking sheet.

Makes 4 dozen cookies.
